<h1>Display Fonts Pack</h1>
<p class="lead">Three variable fonts for editorial, marketing, and publication contexts. Not for body text &mdash; these are display and accent typefaces.</p>

<table>
  <tbody>
    <tr><th>Type</th><td>Font pack (theme tokens only, no JS)</td></tr>
    <tr><th>Theme CSS</th><td><code>packs/fonts-display.theme.css</code></td></tr>
    <tr><th>Total weight</th><td>~430KB (Latin subset, 6 woff2 files)</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<section>
  <h2>Fonts Included</h2>

  <h3>Fraunces &mdash; Display Serif</h3>
  <p>Has a <em>mood axis</em>: <code>WONK</code> (0&ndash;1) introduces deliberate irregularity, <code>SOFT</code> (0&ndash;100) controls stroke softness. Plus <code>wght</code> (100&ndash;900) and <code>opsz</code> (9&ndash;144). Assigns to <code>--font-display</code>.</p>

  <h3>Cormorant &mdash; Editorial Serif</h3>
  <p>Garamond-lineage with the deepest OpenType suite in this stack: swash alternates (<code>swsh</code>), historical ligatures (<code>hist</code>), real small caps (<code>smcp</code>), discretionary ligatures (<code>dlig</code>). Axes: <code>wght</code> (300&ndash;700). Assigns to <code>--vb-font-editorial</code>.</p>
  <p><strong>Caution:</strong> Do not use Cormorant below <code>1.5rem</code> &mdash; it is fragile at small sizes.</p>

  <h3>Bodoni Moda &mdash; Dramatic Contrast</h3>
  <p>High stroke contrast with a wide <code>opsz</code> range (6&ndash;96) &mdash; <code>opsz 6</code> and <code>opsz 96</code> look like different typefaces. Axes: <code>wght</code> (400&ndash;900), <code>opsz</code> (6&ndash;96). Assigns to <code>--vb-font-dramatic</code>.</p>
</section>

